<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work across Brisbane's southern corridor and understand Underwood's buyer profile well. Families who have been comparing properties across Eight Mile Plains, Springwood and Wishart arrive in Underwood with a clear brief: school catchment access, practical amenity within walking distance, and motorway connectivity for commutes in either direction on the Pacific Motorway. When a campaign is positioned around those needs, it attracts the right buyer quickly.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Underwood's commercial precinct, anchored by Underwood Marketplace and the broader Logan Road retail strip, is both an amenity strength and a positioning consideration. Residential streets close to the retail core have excellent walkability but sit on busier arterial roads; the quieter family streets further from the commercial zone are the ones that attract strongest family buyer competition. Properties within Mansfield State High School's catchment boundary consistently draw more buyer inquiry than equivalent homes just outside it, a pattern that every Underwood seller needs to understand before setting a price.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Southern Brisbane Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Marketplace precinct expertise</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">School Catchment Focus</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Consistent family buyer demand</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/springwood" style="color:#c4912a;">Springwood</a>, <a href="/suburbs/eight-mile-plains" style="color:#c4912a;">Eight Mile Plains</a>, <a href="/suburbs/wishart" style="color:#c4912a;">Wishart</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION: FAQ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Underwood.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Underwood?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">School catchment access, proximity to Underwood Marketplace and the Pacific Motorway, and the character of the surrounding residential street are the main value drivers. Homes within Mansfield State High catchment command a consistent premium over comparable properties just outside the boundary. Purely residential streets away from commercial arterials attract the strongest family buyer competition.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Underwood?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Underwood homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb attracts a motivated buyer pool of families comparing it against Eight Mile Plains and Springwood. Properties within school catchment boundaries attract the fastest buyer competition. Accurate pricing relative to comparable southern corridor suburbs is the most important campaign variable.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Underwood?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Underwood offers a convenient southern Brisbane lifestyle anchored by Underwood Marketplace's major retail precinct, with practical Pacific Motorway access for CBD and Gold Coast commuters. Families in the residential pockets enjoy established tree-lined streets, good school options and the commercial convenience that makes Underwood one of the more self-sufficient suburban addresses in the southern corridor.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Underwood a good suburb to sell in right now?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Underwood attracts consistent demand from families in the southern corridor who want practical amenity, school catchment access and motorway connectivity at a realistic price point. The suburb competes directly with Eight Mile Plains and Springwood at similar budgets, so clear positioning and accurate pricing are critical to achieving the best result.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

